The design of the systematic review was 'a priori' individually developed according to the recommendations of the PRISMA statement [39, 40] and AMSTAR measurement tool [41] . The research question was designed following the PICOS scheme [39]: the population are calves and piglets in livestock farming, the intervention is a treatment with medicinal plants, the comparator is no treatment, a placebo or standard treatment, the outcome is the effect of the plant, the study design included in vitro, ex vivo, in vivo and clinical trials. The detailed protocol of the systematic review is provided in the Additional file 1. 